<br>
I have to agree with Froggystyle that because of Verant's idea of how we should roleplay our characters (with the focus on deity, race, class and language restrictions) the server does seem to have more of a focus on alignment (Good vs. Evil) than roleplaying.  I'd hoped it would have more of a focus on free-form roleplaying, but I suspect Verant underestimated the number of people who wanted a server populated by roleplayers, and so they didn't want to scare the non-roleplayers off and end up with an empty server.<br>
<br>
I do not, however, think the Firiona Vie server will suffer from people suggesting that abbreviations like &quot;WTS, WTB, SoW&quot; and the like be avoided in open chat channels -- at least not any more than any server suffers from the green spam in East Commons or Greater Faymart, or the chatter and flames common to any large zone.  <br>
<br>
If being asked not to use abbreviations when conversing with a roleplayer ruins the whole gaming experience for a person -- well, perhaps such a person would be more comfortable without the challenge of dealing with roleplayers, perhaps on Sullon Zek or a regular server? It would seem that there are a lot of people whose roleplaying experiences are &quot;ruined&quot; by the proliferation of abbreviations.   But /ignore works wonders, you know?<br>
<br>
If there were people who were using OOC excessively in open channels -- spamming -- to tell others how to roleplay, I believe that is just as bad as someone spamming l33t-speak -- or anything -- in shout.  (I mean, sheesh, send a /tell, and if the person declines to stop, /ignore them and be on your way.) Either way, spamming an open channel can probably get a response from a Guide via a /petition.<br>
<br>
Do you really think roleplaying (rather than the judgment of, uh, rabid extremists) is too much to bear?<br>
<br>
If roleplaying itself is the problem, and not a select few roleplayers . . . I won't argue that you don't belong here, but I might draw a comparison to moving to a PVP server and expecting to never be slain by another player character. <p><FONT FACE="verdana" SIZE=-2>
