<br>
What is comes down to is that you need to ask yourself: Self, am I willing to put up with this crap to enjoy a new server? If you answer yes, then you wil have to face that this is an issue you will *always* have.<br>
<br>
On a personal note, I think that a little bit of stonewalling is needed to make the server a RP server. I know that it sounds selfish, but the thought that this server still attracts people who think RP is limited to modifying your speech with Old English and those who refuse to RP at all, bothers me.<br>
<br>
I have seen posts that mention forcing RP'ing on people...I believe that is wrong. I think that it would be just as effective to simply mention that you cannot aid or choose not to associate with them because they will &quot;dampen&quot;  your method of play on this server. There is no need to be rude.<br>
<br>
If enough people of like mindset do the above, then those people who are not up to &quot;RP Expectation&quot; will either leave back to their original server or they will find people of thier own with like mindsets.<br>
<br>
Their is no true way for Verant to keep this a Role Playing Server. Only the players can encourage this type of atmosphere. I truly hope that happens... <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/uarios.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Arios</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 74<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(10/15/01 1:06:07 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=48.topic&index=14>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: RP too much to bear?</span><hr size=1> My own humble definition of a role player does not include anyone willing at a moments notice or on the whim of annoyance to step out of character to massively flame someone, be it for RP violations, kill stealing, traning etc.<br>
<br>
If you are a good RPer it will all be in character :-)<br>
<br>
However I think a polite friendly /tell (ooc) chat is appropriate or a /tell in character chat can also work wonders.<br>
<br>
A lot of people who could be turned to the RP side of the force are put off by /shout confrontations that make them dig in and be pissy.<br>
<br>
That said, if you use really silly words in shout around Intra she will look it up in her translation book &quot;The world of language&quot; edited and written by Intra and she will find something humerous to say. Its just her style.<br>
